South Africa has recorded 9 780 new coronavirus infections in the last 24-hour cycle, taking the total number to 1 356 716. The country has also recorded 839 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Tuesday. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in Kwa-Zulu Natal. “Regrettably, we report 839 more COVID-19 related deaths: 102 from Eastern Cape, 20 from the Free State, 48 from Gauteng, 263 from Kwa-Zulu Natal, 238 from Limpopo, 11 from Mpumalanga, 25 from North West, 2 from Northern Cape and 130 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize.  This brings the total number of deaths to 38 288. Recoveries currently stand at 1 144 857. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 7 700 019. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 356 716 , the total number of deaths is 38 288 and the total number of recoveries is 1 144 857. pic.twitter.com/x962nsNe98 — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) January 19, 2021 